masculine /ˈmæskjʊlɪn/

1. ADJ Masculine qualities and things relate to or are considered typical of men, in contrast to women. 男性的 

例： ...masculine characteristics like a husky voice and facial hair. …沙哑的嗓音和面部的胡须之类的男性特征。 

2. ADJ If you say that someone or something is masculine , you mean that they have qualities such as strength or confidence which are considered typical of men. 男子气概的 

例： ...her aggressive, masculine image. …她敢作敢为、男人般的形象。 

3. ADJ In some languages, a masculine noun, pronoun, or adjective has a different form from a feminine or neuter one, or behaves in a different way. (某些语言中的词) 阳性的

</div>

